cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a data-driven approach using convolutional neural networks to improve the image quality of cardiac ultrasound imaging acquired through multi-line acquisition. This involves image processing and machine learning, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves medical imaging, which is covered in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for image processing falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
